Estimates the posterior distribution of individual parameters by Sequential Importance Resampling (SIR)

poso_estim_sir(
  object,
  n_sample = 10000,
  n_resample = 1000,
  return_model = TRUE
)

Arguments

object

A posologyr list, created by the posologyr function.
n_sample

Number of samples from the S-step
n_resample

Number of samples from the R-step
return_model

A boolean. Returns a RxODE model using the estimated ETAs if set to TRUE.

Value

If return_model is set to FALSE, a list of one element: a dataframe $eta of ETAs from the posterior distribution, estimated by Sequential Importance Resampling. If return_model is set to TRUE, a list of the dataframe of the posterior distribution of ETA, and a RxODE model using the estimated distributions of ETAs.
